            . I am servant to Mr. Sayer, of Tower-street. On the 25th of July, about eight o'clock at night, I was going home from Whitechapel with John Clokely, who is seven years old; his father's name is Michael. Opposite <placeName id="t18230910-214-crimeloc1172">Whitechapel church</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-214-crimeloc1172" type="placeName" value="Whitechapel church"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-214-crimeloc1172" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-214-off1170 t18230910-214-crimeloc1172"></join>, a bundle was suddenly snatched from my arm by a man, it contained the property stated in the indictment; and he immediately ran up a court to the right. I saw it in half an hour at Spitalfields watch-house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-214-person1955">
                  THOMAS 
                  BROWN
               <interp inst="t18230910-214-person1955" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-214-person1955" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-214-person1955" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman of Whitechapel. On the 25th of August, I saw the prisoner pass the end of Montague-street into Wentworth-street, with a bundle under his right arm; I followed him, and when I came up with him, he was in the hands of an officer; I first saw him about two hundred yards from Whitechapel church. Almond said, he had dropped a bundle, and I found it about thirty yards from where it was taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-214-person1956">
                  THOMAS 
                  ALMOND
               <interp inst="t18230910-214-person1956" type="surname" value="ALMOND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-214-person1956" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-214-person1956" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , On the 25th of July, about ten o'clock, I stopped the prisoner in Wentworth-street; he dropped the bundle when he saw me, and ran off; he fell, and I took him. The prosecutrix claimed it.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A man ran by me and knocked me in the mud; then Almond laid hold of me and picked up the bundle; it was never in my possession.</p>
